Access a Value by Key
Input: {name: "Juan", age: 25} → access :name
Expected Output: "Juan"

Add a New Key-Value Pair
Input: {a: 1, b: 2} → add c: 3
Expected Output: {a: 1, b: 2, c: 3}

Update a Value
Input: {count: 5} → update to 10
Expected Output: {count: 10}

Delete a Key
Input: {x: 1, y: 2, z: 3} → delete :y
Expected Output: {x: 1, z: 3}

List All Keys
Input: {name: "Ana", age: 30}
Expected Output: [:name, :age]

List All Values
Input: {a: 10, b: 20}
Expected Output: [10, 20]

Check if Key Exists
Input: {name: "Luis", country: "Argentina"} → check :age
Expected Output: false

Merge Two Hashes
Input: {a: 1} and {b: 2}
Expected Output: {a: 1, b: 2}

Count How Many Values Are Even
Input: {a: 2, b: 3, c: 4}
Expected Output: 2

Invert Hash (swap keys and values)
Input: {a: 1, b: 2}
Expected Output: {1 => :a, 2 => :b}